headline: Nuclear Stocks Like NuScale and Oklo Trade Mixed on This Army Announcement
summary: Buzzy nuclear power stocks may have found a new narrative to keep their rally going: Defense contracting.  The Army announced a nuclear power initiative on Tuesday called the Janus Program, which it described as an effort to “deliver resilient, secure, and assured energy to support national defense installations and critical missions.”  The program will build small nuclear reactors, which will be commercially owned and operated.

headline: CIBC launches additional U.S. Canadian Depositary Receipts ("CDRs")
summary: Today CIBC announced six new U.S. Canadian Depositary Receipts ("CDRs"), now listed on the TSX and available for trading. Introduced to investors over four years ago, CIBC has a total of 109 CDRs, spanning four countries, available in market.
